{
  "texts": [
    "Each reference is represented by a label, with the size indicating the number of times the publication is referenced.",
    "Thus, the larger the size, the more frequently the reference is cited.",
    "The distance between two references denotes the probability of those references being cited together.",
    "Therefore, the shorter the distance, the higher the likelihood of them being cited together.",
    "The strongest co-citation links between references are also represented by lines."
  ]
}